headline: Walt Disney (NYSE:DIS) Holds AGM As Shares Remain Flat At 1%
summary: Following the recent annual general meeting, where Walt Disney (NYSE:DIS) shareholders approved a proposal to report on advertising risks but declined those concerning climate and corporate equality, Disney's stock moved by 0.83% last week. During the same period, U.S. markets, including the S&P 500 and Nasdaq, slightly rebounded but more notably climbed overall. While Disney's change was flat in comparison to the broader market's 1.8% weekly rise, its performance reflects a period of market...

headline: How Private Islands Are Reshaping the Cruise Industry
summary: Major cruise lines are leasing private islands and beaches in the Bahamas, keeping spending within their own ecosystems. But some question whether it benefits host nations or takes business away from local ports.
